COVID-19 Filing
In response to the COVID-19 pandemic, on March 6, 2020, Governor Eric Holcomb declared a public health disaster emergency in the state of
Indiana, which is currently still in effect. At that time, Duke Energy Indiana had already voluntarily suspended all disconnections and waived late
payment fees and check return fees. The utility also waived credit card fees for residential customers. The Executive Order requiring utilities in the
state to suspend disconnection of utility service expired July 1, 2020.(a)
